[3] Peru
Date: Fri 8 Jul 2022 16:58 PET
Source: MSN [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, abridged, edited]
https://www.msn.com/es-pe/noticias/otras/minsa-anuncia-que-aumentaron-a-21-los-casos-confirmados-de-viruela-del-mono-en-per-c3-ba/ar-AAZna6O


The Ministry of Health (Minsa) announced this Friday [8 Jul 2022] that up to now there are 21 confirmed monkeypox cases. The agency stated that the patients are from 8 districts in Metropolitan Lima and all have received medical attention.

The cases were detected in the districts of Surco, Jesús María, Pueblo Libre, Cercado de Lima, San Martín de Porres, Los Olivos, Santa Anita and San Miguel.

